annotationA: Ubiquitin conjugating enzyme 7, isoform A; Ubiquitin-protein transferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: defense response to Gram-negative bacterium; positive regulation of innate immune response; protein polyubiquitination; Belongs to the ubiquitin-conjugating enzyme family
annotationB: Autophagy-related 7 is an E1-type ligase for the autophagic ubiquitin-like proteins Atg8a and Atg12. Its roles include autophagosome formation, maintaining neuromuscular function and normal lifespan
